citeinfo.origin: Central Puget Sound Regional Transit Authority (Sound Transit)
citeinfo.title: Sound Transit Link Light Rail Alignments (Central Link, University Link, North Link, Airport Link and Tacoma Link)

descript.abstract:
Contains the entire Central Link, University Link, North Link, and Airport Link light rail alignments from Northgate Mall to SeaTac Airport. Includes identification of alignment segments A-F, areas to be constructed, areas planned for construction, and the orientation of the alignment (e.g. aerial, at-grade, subway, etc.).
Also contains the entire constructed Tacoma Link light rail alignment from the Theater District to the Tacoma Dome.
descript.purpose: Supports Sound Transit's Link light rail line of business function including planning, engineering design, siting, identification and assessment of impacted parcels, environmental assessment, and general mapping. Supports map display and query (in ST Map Explorer) and general mapping agency-wide.
descript.supplinf: Constructed using high-accuracy AutoCAD engineering linework provided by the Link Light Rail department in DXF format. The Office of Policy and Planning GIS Services then converts, processes, and updates the master dataset in ArcGIS personal geodatabase format.
